1. Install Eclipse Kepler
2. Install JDK 1.7.0 (32-bit)
3. Install Glassfish 4.0 (32-bit)
4. Download H2 (32-bit)

4. Create a new Dynamic Web Project 
	4.1 Install New Extension (GlassFish Tools - Oracle)
	4.2 Create a new runtime
		4.2.1 Select GlassFish 4.0 Runtime
		4.2.2 Select the jdk and the directory of glassfish 4.0
	4.3 Dynamic web module version 3.1
	4.4 Default Configuration for GlassFish 4.0

5. Delete the project
6. Import project from Git
	6.1. Clone URL
	6.2. Import existing projects

7. Run as Maven Build...
	7.1 Goals: package
	7.2 Set the JDK
8. Check for Errors under the Problems tab
	8.1 You may have to update the .classpath file

9. Run on Server